orkspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-022: CLI Publish Command\\n2: \\n3: ## Purpose\\n4: \\n5: This proposal implements the `publish` command for the AgentCube Python CLI toolkit. The `publish` command deploys agents to Kubernetes or AgentCube platform using either the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR). This command completes the agent deployment workflow after `pack` and `build` commands.\\n6: \\n7: The goal is to:\\n8: \\n9: 1. **Support dual-provider deployment** - Enable deployment to standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) or AgentCube platform (AgentRuntime CR) via `--provider` flag\\n10: 2. **Handle image preparation** - Prepare container images via local Docker push or accept pre-built image URLs for cloud build mode\\n11: 3. **Manage deployment lifecycle** - Create or patch Kubernetes resources, wait for rollout readiness, and report deployment status\\n12: 4. **Persist deployment metadata** - Update agent metadata with deployment information including agent_id, endpoint URLs, and session configuration\\n13: \\n14: This implementation builds upon the CLI toolkit specification (`cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`) and leverages the Kubernetes provider patterns from `deployment/client-go.md`.\\n15: \\n16: ## Scope\\n17: \\n18: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \\n19: **Language:** Python  \\n2...\n  Line 12: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775868360902,\"sessionID\":\"ses_285ff8cd3ffeYfvxMfbpOKDTUs\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7a00a8d3001GLyzTTtBKDfo35\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7a0094e200109mSGQ3ObVpCg2\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_285ff8cd3ffeYfvxMfbpOKDTUs\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_8b1315fe361a4420afdc8