       │\\n│                    │ agent_metadata.  │                                  │\\n│                    │ yaml             │                                  │\\n│                    └──────────────────┐                                  │\\n│                              │                                    ...\n  Line 25: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775868752703,\"sessionID\":\"ses_285fc3c06ffeoaHprEVR40sEpf\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7a06b2eb001nkZNjZGQSWhQWX\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7a064b920019u13Dwy0xaefaB\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_285fc3c06ffeoaHprEVR40sEpf\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"toolu_tool-a87052b7205b445fbbda4896908db456\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\\n\\n## Metadata\\n\\n| Item | Value |\\n|------|-------|\\n| AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\\n| Language | Python |\\n| Size | M |\\n| Stage | ST-0 |\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\nImplement the `pack` command for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`). The pack command:\\n\\n1. Validates workspace directory structure\\n2. Loads or creates `agent_metadata.yaml` (with fallback to `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`)\\n3. Merges CLI option overrides into metadata\\n4. Validates language compatibility (Python requires `.py` files, Java requires `pom.xml`)\\n5. Processes dependencies (Python: requirements.txt; Java: pom.xml)\\n6. Generates Dockerfile if missing (language-specific templates)\\n7. Updates and saves metadata with pack results\\n8. Reports agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path, dockerfile_path\\n\\n## Out of Scope\\n\\n- Docker image building (handled by `build` command - AR-021)\\n- Kubernetes deployment (handled by `publish` command - AR-022)\\n- Agent invocation (handled by `invoke` command - AR-023)\\n- Status checking (handled by `status` command - AR-024)\\n- Container registry operations\\n- Cloud build mode integration\\n\\n## Dependencies\\n\\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\\n|----------