sj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/design.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-022: CLI publish 命令 Design Document\\n2: \\n3: ## Overview\\n4: \\n5: This design document describes the implementation of the `publish` command for the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The publish command is responsible for deploying packaged agent workloads to either the AgentCube platform (using AgentRuntime custom resources) or standard Kubernetes (using Deployment and Service resources), including container image management and registry integration.\\n6: \\n7: ## Background\\n8: \\n9: The AgentCube CLI toolkit provides a comprehensive command-line interface for managing AI agent lifecycles. The publish command is a critical component that enables developers to deploy their agents to production environments. It supports two deployment targets:\\n10: \\n11: 1. **AgentCube Provider**: Deploys agents using the AgentRuntime custom resource for enhanced features like session management and workload orchestration\\n12: 2. **Kubernetes Provider**: Deploys agents using standard Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service resources for broader compatibility\\n13: \\n14: The publish command must handle various scenarios including:\\n15: - Local image building and pushing to registries\\n16: - Cloud-based image building\\n17: - Image URL specification for pre-built images\\n18: - Registry authentication\\n19: - Version management\\n20: - Dep...\n  Line 28: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775867850411,\"sessionID\":\"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79f8ee840014qozBtke7zJUvV\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79f8c234001pDHYfVvNJAyzw5\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_tool-590692d781bc40798824d390ff4e5d6a\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-gl