 I have all the context I need. Let me create the proposal.md for AR-022 (CLI publish command) following the same structure as AR-020:\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775867779357,\"end\":1775867779357}}}\n  Line 18: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775868034116,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79f7d91f001wjEJKCclVdVCmW\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79f7c977001Z1OllRvA536yev\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"toolu_428eee7c48464727b3c9cd68\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md\",\"content\":\"# AR-022: CLI Publish Command\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThis proposal implements the `publish` command for the AgentCube Python CLI toolkit. The `publish` command deploys agents to Kubernetes or AgentCube platform using either the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR). This command completes the agent deployment workflow after `pack` and `build` commands.\\n\\nThe goal is to:\\n\\n1. **Support dual-provider deployment** - Enable deployment to standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) or AgentCube platform (AgentRuntime CR) via `--provider` flag\\n2. **Handle image preparation** - Prepare container images via local Docker push or accept pre-built image URLs for cloud build mode\\n3. **Manage deployment lifecycle** - Create or patch Kubernetes resources, wait for rollout readiness, and report deployment status\\n4. **Persist deployment metadata** - Update agent metadata with deployment information including agent_id, endpoint URLs, and session configuration\\n\\nThis implementation builds upon the CLI toolkit specification (`cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`) and leverages the Kubernetes provider patterns from `deployment/client-go.md`.\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \\n**Language:** Python  \\n**Size:** L\\n\\nThis AR covers:\\n\\n- **In scope:**\\n  - `PublishRuntime` class implementation with all specified methods\\n  - `publish` Typer command with all specified options (workspace, version, image_url, credentials, provider, node_p...\n  Line 21: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775868039198,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79fbc7f3001JbIYthfanh0NXt\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79fbbc85001zomempwyJRK4pJ\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Created `changes/AR-022/proposal.md` with the complete implementation proposal for the CLI `publish` command including:\\n\\n- **PublishRuntime** class with dual-provider support (AgentCube CR and standard K8s)\\n- **AgentCubeProvider** for AgentRuntime CR operations\\n- **KubernetesProvider** for Deployment/Service operations  \\n- **DockerService** enhancements for image build/push\\n- CLI `publish` command with all specified options\\n- Unit and integration test strategies\\n- Full acceptance criteria aligned with the spec\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775868039196,\"end\":1775868039196}}}\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-029_ST-2.log:\n  Line 10: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775867725317,\"sessionID\":\"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79f7020b001nxkA2ORdjMAgGF\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79f6f9d6001Fu6G4kEqQIygUC\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_fe3ce46939c842a2b6de07bb\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-026: K8s/AgentCube Provider — Delta Spec\\n2: \\n3: ## Context\\n4: \\n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\\n6: - **Language:** Python\\n7: - **Size:** M\\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\\n9: \\n10: ## Scope\\n11: \\n12: This delta spec covers `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes — their deployment, status retrieval, namespace management, name sanitization, CRD availability checks, and K8s client initialization error handling. Provider selection in CLI publish/status/invoke commands is also specified.\\n13: \\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: ## KubernetesProvider\\n17: \\n18: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider constructor\\n19: The system SHALL initialize `KubernetesProvider` with namespace, verbose flag, and optional kubeconfig path.\\n20: \\n21: #### Scenario: default constructor\\n22: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider()` is called with no arguments\\n23: - **WHEN** the instance is created\\n24: - **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\\\"default\\\"`, `verbose` to `False`, and `kubeconfig` to `None`\\n25: \\n26: #### Scenario: custom kubeconfig\\n27: - **GIVEN** a custom kubeconfig path is provided\\n28: - **WHEN** the instance is created\\n29: - **THEN** the system SHALL load the K8s configuration from that path\\n30: \\n31: #### Scenario: kubeconfig not found\\n32: - **GIVEN** no kubeconfig file exists at the default or specified ...\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z_logs/AR-022_ST-3.log:\n  Line 4: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775867568657,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79f4a1dc001usQTd1Sl9RaLz1\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79f48e980018lLls0ch73Q0jg\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_tool-ebab951c0f824fada8bd7c32c159eadf\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-gl