IfY\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2861ba594ffea8eHQyIpK9A7AF\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"toolu_bc7879a175464a9a9ea55bb9\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"path\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark\",\"pattern\":\"AR-025\"},\"output\":\"Found 127 matches (showing first 100)\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z_logs/AR-025_ST-5.log:\\n  Line 8: {\\\"type\\\":\\\"tool_use\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":1775866166232,\\\"sessionID\\\":\\\"ses_28620f443ffeOwB10PccdNhCR2\\\",\\\"part\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"prt_d79df2c5d001fVA3Iav40dgWza\\\",\\\"messageID\\\":\\\"msg_d79df1d13001aFIJTQnx7NkUmq\\\",\\\"sessionID\\\":\\\"ses_28620f443ffeOwB10PccdNhCR2\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"tool\\\",\\\"tool\\\":\\\"read\\\",\\\"callID\\\":\\\"toolu_c055f9be1d0546ce81d38def\\\",\\\"state\\\":{\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\",\\\"input\\\":{\\\"filePath\\\":\\\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md\\\"},\\\"output\\\":\\\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\\\\n<type>file</type>\\\\n<content>\\\\n1: # AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型增强\\\\n2: \\\\n3: ## Summary\\\\n4: \\\\n5: 增强 MetadataService 和数据模型，实现完整的元数据生命周期管理和验证功能。\\\\n6: \\\\n7: ## Purpose\\\\n8: \\\\n9: ### Background\\\\n10: \\\\n11: `AgentMetadata` 和 `MetadataService` 是 CLI 核心的元数据管理组件。当前实现存在以下问题:\\\\n12: 1. `AgentMetadata` 位于 `services` 包，而非 `models` 包\\\\n13: 2. 缺少 `update_metadata` 方法\\\\n14: 3. 缺少语言特定的工作区验证\\\\n15: 4. `MetadataOptions` 缺少 `from_options` 类方法\\\\n16: \\\\n17: ### Goal\\\\n18: \\\\n19: 1. 迁移 AgentMetadata 到 models 包统一管理\\\\n20: 2. 实现完整的 MetadataService CRUD 操作\\\\n21: 3. 添加语言特定验证逻辑\\\\n22: 4. 增强 MetadataOptions\\\\n23: \\\\n24: ### Value\\\\n25: \\\\n26: - **模块化**: 数据模型与业务逻辑分离\\\\n27: - **可维护性**: 统一的模型定义位置\\\\n28: - **完整性**: 完整的元数据生命周期支持\\\\n29: - **可验证性**: 语言特定工作区验证\\\\n30: \\\\n31: ---\\\\n32: \\\\n33: ## Scope\\\\n34: \\\\n35:...\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z_logs/AR-021_ST-2.log:\n  Line 16: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775866196846,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79dfb346001JykjwnrAZ5LVUk\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79dfaa8d001hsgkbfVTieirTF\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_tool-5788d34a8a7541259f71c1ed9f66fbe2\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # delta-spec.md — AR-020: CLI pack 命令\\n2: \\n3: ## Module: `cmd/cli`\\n4: \\n5: ## Delta Overview\\n6: \\n7: Add the `pack` command to the AgentCube CLI for validating and preparing agent workspaces, merging CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generating Dockerfiles, and reporting paths.\\n8: \\n9: ---\\n10: \\n11: ## REQ-001: Pack command initialization\\n12: \\n13: ### Requirement: Pack command registration and default options\\n14: \\n15: System SHALL provide a `pack` command that validates and prepares agent workspaces with configurable options.\\n16: \\n17: **Acceptance Criteria:**\\n18: - Command name: `pack`\\n19: - Supports workspace path specification\\n20: - Supports metadata field overrides via CLI options\\n21: - Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\\n22: - Supports custom output path specification\\n23: \\n24: **Scenarios:**\\n25: \\n26: #### Scenario 1.1: Command registration and default options\\n27: - **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI Typer application is initialized\\n28: - **WHEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack` without options\\n29: - **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\\n30:   - `workspace`: `\\\".\\\"` (current directory)\\n31:   - `agent_name`: `None`\\n32:   - `language`: `None`\\n33:   - `entrypoint`: `None`\\n34:   - `port`: `None`\\n35:   - `build_mode`: `None`\\n36:   - `description`: `None`\\n37:   - `output`: `None`\\n38:   - `verbo...\n  Line 36: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775866327108,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79e1afe4001a0B7KGjDvwuC70\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79dffb16001mD86CCmjB27RQB\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"toolu_tool-d814f7f9a82c43b5b28b2ee434b0f13f\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# AR-021 Delta Specification: CLI build 命令\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nImplement the `build` command for the AgentCube CLI to build container images from packaged agent workspaces, supporting local Docker builds and cloud provider builds with proxy support, version management, and comprehensive error handling.\\n\\n## Requirements\\n\\n### Requirement: Build command registration and default options\\n\\nThe system SHALL provide a `build` command that builds container images from packaged agent workspaces with configurable options.\\n\\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\\n- Command name: `build`\\n- Supports workspace path specification\\n- Supports proxy configuration for dependency resolution\\n- Supports cloud provider selection\\n- Supports custom output path for build artifacts\\n- Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\\n\\n**Scenarios:**\\n\\n#### Scenario 1.1: Command registration and default options\\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI Typer application is initialized\\n- **WHEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube build` without options\\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\\n  - `workspace`: `\\\".\\\"` (current directory)\\n  - `proxy`: `None`\\n  - `cloud_provider`: `None`\\n  - `output`: `None`\\n  - `verbose`: `False`\\n\\n#### Scenario 1.2: Command option validation\\n- **GIVEN** the user provides CLI options\\n- **WHEN** options include `--workspace`, `--proxy`, `--cloud-provider`, `--output`, `--verbose`\\n- **THEN** the system SHALL accept all valid option values:\\n  - `workspace`: string path to workspace directory\\n  - `proxy`: string URL or None\\n  - `cloud_provider`: string provider name or None\\n  - `output`: string path or None\\n  - `...\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z_logs/AR-025_ST-3.log:\n  Line 13: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775865992488,\"sessionID\":\"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79dc91d4001cdiJ9Vy8JnO1M4\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79dc82080013dpmoAR3SImoSK\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_7959e1caf1364ddf8abf0324\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-021 — CLI Build Command\\n2: \\n3: - **AR ID**: AR-021\\n4: - **Module**: cmd/cli\\n5: - **Language**: Python\\n6: - **Size**: M\\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\\n8: \\n9: ## 1. Architecture\\n10: \\n11: ### 1.1 Overview\\n12: \\n13: AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) is a Python-based command-line tool for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes. The CLI uses Typer for command parsing and provides a rich user experience with Rich library.\\n14: \\n15: ### 1.2 Package Structure\\n16: \\n17: ```\\n18: cmd/cli/\\n19: ├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping\\n20: ├── agentcube/\\n21: │   ├── __init__.py                             # Package version __version__, exports app, runtimes\\n22: │   ├── cli/\\n23: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # CLI subpackage marker\\n24: │   │   └── main.py                             # Typer app, all commands, _handle_error, version_callback\\n25: │   ├── models/\\n26: │   │   └── pack_models.py                      # MetadataOptions dataclass\\n27: │   ├── runtime/\\n28: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # Re-exports runtimes + MetadataOptions\\n29: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py                     # PackRuntime\\n30: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py                    #...\n  Line 20: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775866057925,\"sessionID\":\"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79dcdd69001nGScP3nw4Zik2W\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79dcb5ad001doOJkcEzFWv2v8\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"edit\",\"callID\":\"toolu_cc6a6dbc71094540b678d60d\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md\",\"newString\":\"---\\n\\n# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\\n\\n- **AR ID**: AR-025\\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\\n- **Language**: Python\\n- **Size**: M\\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\\n\\n## 1. Architecture\\n\\n### 1.1 Overview\\n\\nMetadataService provides centralized management of agent metadata throughout the CLI lifecycle. It handles loading, validation, saving, and updating of `AgentMetadata` configuration files that track agent state from packaging through deployment.\\n\\n### 1.2 Package Structure\\n\\n```\\nagentcube/\\n├── models/\\n│   └── pack_models.py          # MetadataOptions dataclass\\n├── services/\\n│   └── metadata_service.py      # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\\n└── runtime/\\n    └── pack_runtime.py         # Uses MetadataService\\n```\\n\\n## 2. Data Models\\n\\n### 2.1 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\\n\\nThe core data model representing agent configuration and state.\\n\\n```python\\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\\n\\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\\\"Unique name identifying the agent\\\")\\n    description: Optional[str] = None\\n    language: str = \\\"python\\\"\\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\\\"Command to launch the agent\\\")\\n    port: int = 8080\\n    build_mode: str = \\\"local\\\"\\n    region: Optional[str] = None\\n    version: Optional[str] = None\\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\\n    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = \\\"requirements.txt\\\"\\n    reg...\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z_logs/AR-020_ST-7.log:\n  Line 24: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775865897843,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286252d1cffeKPg870jV0WDBP8\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79db234d001sMhRPxlYep4dO3\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79db1b80001uCi505EevC0z7x\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286252d1cffeKPg870jV0WDBP8\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_tool-21c371810dc94baa8ab02d0e9d908ff9\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 Implementation Tasks\\n2: \\n3: **Module**: `cmd/cli`\\n4: **Language**: Python\\n5: **Size**: M\\n6: **Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\\n7: \\n8: ## Task Breakdown\\n9: \\n10: ### Task 1: Create cmd/cli directory structure\\n11: - [ ] Create cmd/cli directory\\n12: - [ ] Create cmd/cli/pyproject.toml\\n13: - [ ] Create cmd/cli/README.md\\n14: - [ ] Create cmd/cli/.gitignore\\n15: - [ ] Ver